                <head>260. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On March 24, 1965, Secretary of Agriculture <persName corresp="#p_FOL1">Orville
                        Freeman</persName> signed a Protocol for the Extension of the International
                    Wheat Agreement, 1962. The Protocol provided for the extension of the 1962
                    Agreement, which would expire on July 31, 1965, until July 31, 1966. The U.S.
                    Senate gave its advice and consent to the Protocol on June 15, which entered
                    into force for the United States on July 16 (Parts I and III–VII) and August 1
                    (Part II). For text of the Protocol, see 16 <gloss target="#t_UST1">UST</gloss>
                    1010. Documentation on the ratification of the Protocol is in Department of
                    State, Central Files, INCO–WHEAT 4.</p>
            </div>
